          "COMMENT": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "-Abstract:  Angular Distributions of a",
                "6-Li(P,ALPHA)3-He Reaction were Measured at Six Angles",
                "For 140 KeV Proton Energy Using Nuclear Track",
                "Detectors.  The Measurements were Carried Out Over",
                "60-160 Lab. Angles in 20 Increments Using a Scattering",
                "Chamber of Beam Line of the 350 Kv  Accelerator.",
                "Semiconductor Silicon Surface Barrier Detector was",
                "Placed at +160 Degrees and was Used As a Monitor. The",
                "Results have Shown That the Cr-39 Detector has",
                "Excellent Capabilities to Distinguish 1.4-2.7 MeV Alpha",
                "+ 3-He Particles from the Reaction and 8-9.4 MeV",
                "Alpha-Particles from the 7-Li(P,A)4-He Reaction Through",
                "Their Track Diameters.  However,It was not Possible to",
                "Distinguish Between the 2.3 MeV 3-He Ions and the 1.7",
                "MeV 4-He Ions from the 6-Li(P,A)3-He Reaction from",
                "Their Track Diameter Measurements, But It was Possible",
                "To Differentiate Between the Two, from the Darker",
                "Contrast of the 3-He Particles Caused by Its Deeper",
                "Tracks As Compared to Those of 4-He."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "SAMPLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "The Lithium Targets were Prepared by Evaporating 2400",
                "Angstrom Thick Li-F Layers on 1.5 Millimeters Thick",
                "Tantalum Sheets."
